      "side": 1,
      "message": "for the record, I\u0027ve looked at the Linux disassembly for this line, and it seems to perform a \"lock subq\" instruction, despite the std::memory_order_relaxed. I\u0027m not sure whether this is a toolchain bug, or something I don\u0027t understand here :-|",
      "revId": "3c3c2969f230d7ac03824a1d745e9b4f23a9b051",
